# Senior architecture lite

Write code that is easy to read, test, and change without over-engineering.

Guidelines:

- Keep UI components focused on rendering and user interaction.
- Keep SharePoint/Graph/API calls in existing service/repository layers when present.
- Keep mapping between transport models and view/domain models explicit when the repo already does so.
- Prefer pure functions for formatting, filtering, validation, and state transitions.
- Prefer small named functions over complex inline logic.
- Avoid duplicate code; extract only when there are at least two real call sites or a clear existing pattern.
- Avoid speculative abstractions.
- Do not add a new layer just because a textbook architecture suggests it.
- Match existing dependency direction.

When modifying architecture, explain:

- why the existing pattern is not enough
- migration scope
- risk
- validation approach
